The paper deals with cryptographic hash functions and their applications in remote verification tasks, which are typically studied in the computer security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT) sub-categories. The paper also uses concepts from data structures (cs.DS), computational complexity (cs.CC), and distributed computing (cs.DC) to prove their result. Therefore, these sub-categories are also likely to be relevant to the paper.
